72509 {source=\"BIRNLEX:1776\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Brodmann_area_44\nis_a: UBERON:0013529 ! Brodmann area\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000956 ! cerebral cortex\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/2917\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0006854\nname: distal straight tubule postmacula segment\nsynonym: \"cortical thick ascending limb of Henle's loop\" EXACT [MA:th]\nsynonym: \"kidney cortex loop of Henle ascending limb thick segment\" EXACT [MA:th]\nsynonym: \"renal cortex loop of Henle ascending limb thick segment\" EXACT [MA:th]\nsynonym: \"renal cortex thick ascending limb\" EXACT [MA:th]\nxref: EMAPA:28402\nxref: MA:0002615\nis_a: UBERON:0007685 ! region of nephron tubule\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001291 {source=\"MA\"} ! thick ascending limb of loop of Henle\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0006853 {source=\"MA\"} ! renal cortex tubule\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://sourceforge.net/tracker/?func=detail&aid=3123598&group_id=76834&atid=1205376\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0009776\nname: intermediate reticular formation\nsynonym: \"intermediate reticular formations\" RELATED OMO:0003004 [ZFA:0000219]\nxref: TAO:0000219\nxref: ZFA:0000219\nis_a: UBERON:0007245 {source=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165\"} ! nuclear complex of neuraxis\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002559 {source=\"GOC:pr\", source=\"brainspan.org\"} ! medullary reticular formation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://sourceforge.net/tracker/?func=detail&atid=440764&aid=3413098&group_id=36855\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0011253\nname: obsolete gland of anal sac\ncomment: Obsoleted as it seems to refer to the same concept as 'gland of anal canal'.\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3159\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: UBERON:0004760\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0012184\nname: obsolete tunica vasculosa plexus\ncomment: obsolete term deriving from MA to NCITA mappings.\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://sourceforge.net/tracker/?func=detail&aid=3580301&group_id=76834&atid=1205376\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nconsider: MA:0001284\nconsider: NCIT:C33823\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035075\nname: obsolete thymus subunit\ncomment: Obsoleted as it is redundant with 'thymus lobe'.\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3158\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: UBERON:0005483\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:1200000\nname: ileocecal fold\ndef: \"A fold of peritoneum between the ileum and cecum. The upper border of the ileocecal fold is fixed to the ileum opposite its mesenteric attachment, and the lower border passes over the ileocecal junction to join the mesentery of the appendix (and sometimes the appendix itself as well). Behind the ileocecal fold is the inferior ileocecal fossa.\" [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ileocecal_fold]\nsynonym: \"ileocaecal fold\" EXACT []\nxref: FMA:16532\nis_a: UBERON:0034696 ! fold of peritoneum\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165 ! Christopher J. Mungall\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2025-01-15T10:00:00Z\" xsd:dateTime\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3326\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:2000597\nname: obsolete telencephalic tracts\ncomment: Obsoleted as it is redundant with 'white matter of telencephalon'.\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3160\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: UBERON:0011299\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:2005411\nname: obsolete common crus\ncomment: Obsoleted as it is redundant with 'common crus of semircular duct'.\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3161\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: UBERON:0013764\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:3010146\nname: obsolete lacrimal\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. Investing bone in non-teleos